entry.title: CR23: Fix background behind toolbar rounded corners.
entry.content:
When the toolbar draws its rounded corners, it leaves behind some pixels

that are unpainted. This CL adds two child Views to ToolbarView that sit

behind the top-left and top-right corners. These views are not affected

by the clip path. The views draw the same background as the tabstrip.



This CL makes two small supporting changes:

* It moves some logic in TopContainerBackground to a standalone method

to avoid code duplication for painting image-themed backgrounds.

* It adds a listener to update the background views on window active

state change.



Note that the toolbar already repaints on theme change so no additional

listener is needed for that case.

entry.title: Revert "[dPWA] Support uninstallation of individual install URLs for externally managed web apps"
entry.content:
This reverts commit f59f7ca684b35e947a2d232fe69e0f34048fc943.



Reason for revert: Causing crashes on Canary. crbug.com/1449395



Original change's description:

> [dPWA] Support uninstallation of individual install URLs for externally managed web apps

>

> There was no code path for removing an install URL from an externally

> managed web app. Instead we were removing the associated install

> source entirely. This CL fixes that behavior.

>

> WebAppUninstallCommand's queue processing has been converted into

> a sequential async loop rather than a batch uninstall job starter.

> This is for simpler reasoning about multiple async mutations.

> Performance is not under consideration here as it is an uninstallation

> action.

entry.title: Define __rust_no_alloc_shim_is_unstable to use our allocator shims
entry.content:
https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/73632#issuecomment-1563462239:

```

As of #86844 (scheduled for the 1.71 release) if you are directly

linking the rlibs of the standard library rather than letting rustc

handle linking, you will now need to define a static named

`__rust_no_alloc_shim_is_unstable` which is at least 1 byte big. In

addition if you are using `#[global_allocator]`, you must stop defining

`__rust_alloc`, `__rust_dealloc`, `__rust_realloc` and

`__rust_alloc_zeroed` as they are now directly defined by the

`#[global_allocator]` expansion rather than as part of the allocator

shim. If you are using the default allocator in libstd you will need

to keep defining them though.

```



We use the default allocator, so we can keep using our C++ shims as

long as we define this new symbol.

entry.title: shortcuts: Filter kDisabledByUnavailableKeys accels in edit-dialog
entry.content:
* Problem: When user edit the accelerators in the dialog, the

accelerators that should be hidden(kDisabledByUnavailableKeys) shows

again.



* Reason:

When dialog is first opened, showDialog() from accelerator_row will

be called, and will dispatch 'show-edit-dialog' event with

'accelerators: this.acceleratorInfos', then showDialog(e:

ShowEditDialogEvent) is called from shortcut_customization_app.ts.

Therefore, The dialog_accelerators are derived from accelerator_row

and already filtered(filter is done in subsection then pass to row).



However, when user edit the accelerator, it won't get the

dialog_accelerators from accelerator_row, instead it gets from

onRequestUpdateAccelerators(), the updatedAccels don't filter out

the kDisabledByUnavailableKeys, thats' why it shows those accels

again.



* Fix: Filter the kDisabledByUnavailableKeys in

accelerator_edit_dialog.

entry.title: blink: avoid unnecessary processing when class attribute changes
entry.content:
When the class attribute changes Element does the following:



1. Updates `class` on the ElementData.

2. Calls to the StyleEngine.



If the ElementData is shared, and the class data is already up

to date date, then 1 is unnecessary.



Additionally, if in the inactive document, then 2 is unnecessary.

2 is unnecessary in this case because of an early out in the

StyleEngine:

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/style_engine.cc;l=1155;drc=90b428dcab63b652cc91107b81d2758270e92ac0



This takes one of the bits in ElementData to track whether the

class is dirty. As the bitfield is 32 bits, I'm reducing the

number of attributes by half (2^28th to 2^27th). This also ensures

we only create ShareableElementData if the number of attributes

fits in the bitmask.

entry.title: Add scrim to Welcome Tour [Part 1].
entry.content:
This CL adds a `WelcomeTourScrim` class which applies a scrim to the

help bubble container of all root windows while in existence. Though

not done in this CL, a `WelcomeTourScrim` instance will be owned by

the `WelcomeTourController` while the Welcome Tour is in progress.
